<TITLE> Chelsea on guard to avoid another Cluj upset </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Oct 1 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Champions League newcomers CFR Cluj will represent dangerous opposition to last season's runners-up Chelsea on Wednesday, said coach Luiz Felipe Scolari. The Romanian team caused a mighty shock two weeks ago by winning 2-1 at AS Roma. "We will rely on our teamwork and team spirit against a very dangerous opponent," Scolari told reporters ahead of Chelsea's visit to Cluj. Girondins Bordeaux, who lost their opening match 4-0 at Chelsea, host Roma in Wednesday's other Group A game. Cypriots Anorthosis Famagusta, who drew 0-0 with Werder Bremen on their Champions League debut, entertain Panathinaikos in Group B having already beaten their Greek rivals Olympiakos Piraeus in the last qualifying round. Inter Milan, seeking to become European champions for the first time since 1965, host a rampant Werder Bremen, who have scored 10 goals in their last two Bundesliga matches. Liverpool meet PSV Eindhoven at Anfield in confident mood for their Group D tie after an unbeaten start to the season while Atletico Madrid take on Olympique Marseille. In Group C, Sporting Lisbon face Basel and Shakhtar Donetsk play Barcelona
